title: TU Power Poll: Trinity, Bolles, Raines stay put in Week 7
text:
TU Power Poll: Trinity, Bolles, Raines stay put in Week 7 
Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 8:38 pm | updated Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 9:05 pm BRUCE LIPSKY/The Times-Union Trinity's Daequantae Showers dives into the end zone in front of UC's DJ Stubbs during the Conquerors 35-20 win on Sept. 11. 
POWER POLL 
Last week’s rankings in parentheses. All games 7 p.m. Friday unless indicated 
1. (1) TRINITY CHRISTIAN (5-0), CLASS 3A 
Last week: d. Providence, 43-0 
This week: at Tallahassee Godby (2-3) 
Glance: The Conquerors thundered on last week, hammering the Stallions for their 25th consecutive district win dating back to the 2007 season. They visit Godby, a team they’ve split with the last two seasons. 
2. (2) BOLLES (6-0), CLASS 4A 
Last week: d. West Nassau, 56-6 
This week: Columbia (4-1), 7:30 
Glance: The Bulldogs get one of their biggest challenges of the season against the Tigers. If they win this, there’s no challenge again until Week 10 at Raines. 
3. (3) RAINES (5-0), CLASS 4A 
Last week: Off 
This week: First Coast (1-4) 
Glance: The Vikings have lit teams up this year. Can they maintain that edge against the first formidable defense they will see this season? 
4. (4) ST. AUGUSTINE (6-0), CLASS 6A 
Last week: d. Englewood, 45-6 
This week: Off 
Glance: The Yellow Jackets won their 49th consecutive district game last week and reach their bye week with a very good shot at a 10-0 season. 
5. (5) MANDARIN (5-0), CLASS 8A 
Last week: Off 
This week: at Wolfson (0-6) 
Glance: The Mustangs’ playoff fate will be determined with games over the next three weeks, at Sandalwood (Oct. 16), Spruce Creek (Oct. 23) and at Flagler Palm Coast (Oct. 30). 
6. (6) UNIVERSITY CHRISTIAN (4-1), CLASS 2A 
Last week: d. Harvest, 61-0 
This week: Eagle’s View (1-4), 7:30 
Glance: The Christians, ranked No. 1 in the state, can wrap up a District 2-2A title next week against Cedar Creek Christian. 
7. (7) SANDALWOOD (6-0), CLASS 8A 
Last week: d. Flagler Palm Coast, 21-7 
This week: Lee (3-2) 
Glance: Another good challenge for the Saints as they continue their march toward a potential unbeaten showdown with Mandarin next week. 
8. (8) OAKLEAF (5-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week : d. Fleming Island, 30-16 
This week: Off 
Glance: The Knights have recovered well since a loss to Gainesville Buchholz in Week 4. Offensively, they’ve looked sharp since. 
9. (9) COLUMBIA (4-1), CLASS 7A 
Last week: Off 
This week: at Bolles (6-0), 7:30 
Glance: The Tigers lost their last time out in a 44-41 setback to Escambia. Playing at Bolles is a brutal welcome back from the bye-week game. 
10. (10) UNION COUNTY (5-0), CLASS 1A 
Last week: Off 
This week: Hawthorne (4-2), 7:30 
Glance: Arguably Union County’s most difficult District 6-1A game. A win here is a major step toward a district title. 

On the bubble: Ponte Vedra (5-1), Class 5A.
